The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the Johnson Space Center in Houston, Texas, highlighting the renewed focus on American leadership in space. He praised the work of NASA and its employees, as well as the vision and support of President Donald Trump and the Congress. Pence emphasized the commitment to return to the moon and explore Mars, and announced plans for the establishment of a United States Space Force. He also mentioned the importance of partnerships with private companies and the need to strengthen American security in space. Pence assured the audience that NASA will receive the necessary funding and support to continue its important work.